Which of the following are valid Boolean Expressions that could be used in an
if
conditional statement or
while
loop?

a. var = 22  No, this is not a boolean value, it is setting a variable.
b.var > 22  Can be True or False, so yes.
c.string_var == ‘hello’ Can be True or False, so yes.
d.result = num1 + num2 / 3 No, not a bool value.
e.total == num1 + num1 Yes, this be a bool value.
f.(my_var) No.
g.False Is a bool value, yes.
h.input(‘Enter a number:’) No
i.result%2 No
j.user_text = input(‘Enter a number:’) No